<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-567-969  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 567 969.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Nov 5 1990 v7 n44 p10(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ZSoft announces Windows 3.0 version of paint program. (ZSoft Corp.andO;introduces Publisher's Paintbrush 2.0) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pompili, Tony.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   ZSoft Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Microsoft Windows 3.0 (Graphical user interface) (Computerprograms)Publisher's Paintbrush 2.0 (Computer graphics software) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Graphics SoftwareProduct IntroductionGraphical User Interface.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Tony PompiliandM;ZSoft Corp. last week unveiled a Windows 3.0 version of its popular PCPaintbrush graphics program designed to exploit the environment's memoryscheme.andM;Publisher's Paintbrush 2.0 takes advantage of Windows' enhanced mode to editlarge graphics in virtual memory and uses its own proprietary virtual memoryto access graphics across multiple hard disks, according to ZSoft officialsin Marietta, Ga.andM;With version 2.0, users can open graphics in separate windows and tap a zoomfeature to edit graphics at pixel level.andP;  Editing features include blend,sharpen, and tint adjustments.andP;  Users can tap the filters to automaticallysharpen edges, adjust colors and reduce spots.andM;Another major addition to the upgrade is the built-in scanner-controlfeature.andP;  Version 2.0 will allow users to scan images directly into theprogram, unlike many image-editing programs that require a separate scanningsoftware to accomplish the same task, the officials said.andM;New paint tools include gradient files and a feature to create backgroundsmade of tiles of colors and patterns.andP;  Traditional line, curve andgeometric-shape drawing tools are also included.andM;Publisher's Paintbrush 2.0, slated for release early next year, is priced at$495; current users can upgrade for $75.andO;</TEXT></DOC>